CONFIRMED genuine skip (#3) — needs removed Python generator/coroutine handler bodies + self.execute().

test.ini uses a py= body (`REMAP=M405 py=body_405`) plus [PYTHON] TOPLEVEL, and the
handlers (remap.py) are Python GENERATORS that interleave running g-code strings and
yielding for motion to finish:

    def body_405(self, **words):
        self.execute("(body_M405 begin)")
        self.execute("G0 Y1"); yield interpreter.INTERP_EXECUTE_FINISH
        self.execute("G0 Y2"); yield interpreter.INTERP_EXECUTE_FINISH
        ...

Two removed features are needed and neither has a C interp_ext equivalent:
 (1) `self.execute("...")` — running arbitrary g-code strings from inside a handler;
     interp_ctx exposes no execute-string accessor.
 (2) a generator/coroutine handler that yields INTERP_EXECUTE_FINISH multiple times,
     keeping Python local state across each re-entry.

Note interp_ext CAN return a single INTERP_EXT_EXECUTE_FINISH, but that alone cannot
reproduce the multi-yield coroutine + self.execute pattern this test is about, and
gomc rejects `py=` remaps at parse anyway. Genuine removal, obsolete by design.
